capture source:\n\n```text\nsha256(agent + NUL + provider-session-id)\n```\n\nor, when provider session id is missing:\n\n```text\nsha256(agent + NUL + canonical-transcript-path-bytes)\n```\n\nNo new CLI option is added yet for joining an existing GitButler session.\n\nSession-level keys:\n\n```text\n:schema = gitbutler.agent-session.v1\n:updated-at = <capture timestamp>\n:record-hashes = set<sha256:record>\n:transcript = list<TranscriptEnvelope JSON>\n:source-keys = set<source-key>\n```\n\nSource-specific keys:\n\n```text\n:source:<source-key>:agent\n:source:<source-key>:provider\n:source:<source-key>:model\n:source:<source-key>:cwd\n:source:<source-key>:tool-version\n:source:<source-key>:provider-session-key\n:source:<source-key>:path\n:source:<source-key>:size\n:source:<source-key>:sha256\n:source:<source-key>:last-record-index\n:source:<source-key>:captured-at\n```\n\n`provider-session-key` is hashed, not the raw provider session id.\n\n## Transcript Envelope Changes\nKeep one ordered `:transcript` list per durable session. Each entry remains one redacted JSON envelope, but the envelope becomes more useful to future readers.\n\nAdd these normalized fields:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"schema\": \"gitbutler.agent-transcript.v1\",\n  \"session_key\": \"sha256-...\",\n  \"source_key\": \"sha256-...\",\n  \"agent\": \"codex\",\n  \"provider\": \"openai\",\n  \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\",\n  \"provider_session_key\": \"sha256-...\",\n  \"source_record_index\": 0,\n  \"source_record_hash\": \"sha256:...\",\n  \"source_timestamp\": \"...\",\n  \"source_event_kind\": \"...\",\n  \"event_category\": \"message\",\n  \"role\": \"user\",\n  \"content_text\": \"redacted normalized message text if easy to extract\",\n  \"tool_name\": null,\n  \"turn_id\": null,\n  \"message_id\": null,\n  \"parent_message_id\": null,\n  \"cwd\": null,\n  \"git_branch\": null,\n  \"source_record_redacted\": false,\n  \"source_record_redactions\": 0,\n  \"source_record\": {}\n}\n```\n\nUse minimal extraction rules:\n- `event_category`: one of `session`, `context`, `message`, `tool`, or `other`.\n- Codex message text: string values from obvious payload text/content paths only.\n- Claude message text: `message.content` string, or joined text blocks from `message.content[]`.\n- `tool_name`: first obvious tool name when present; otherwise `null`.\n- Preserve the redacted `source_record` for provenance and future backfill.\n\nDo not add rich planning artifacts, summaries, branch refs, PR refs, or publishable `agent:*` keys in this step.\n\n## Implementation Notes\n- Rename the current writer input around the new concept if helpful, e.g. `SessionCapture` keeps session-level data plus one `SourceCapture` worth of provenance.\n- Keep parser branches closed and explicit for Codex/Claude. Do not introduce a plugin/provider trait.\n- Keep dedupe behavior:\n  - `:record-hashes` dedupes record-derived metadata.\n  - transcript append dedupe is rebuilt from existing envelope `source_record_hash` values.\n  - duplicate records within one run are skipped once.\n- Update tests to use the new key layout; no migration path is required because this is still hidden POC storage.\n\n## Test Plan\n- `cargo test -p but-agentlog`\n  - session index contains the derived `session-key`\n  - storage no longer nests sessions under `<agent>:<session-key>`\n  - source-specific keys are written and updated on repeated/growing capture\n  - transcript envelopes include `session_key`, `source_key`, `provider_session_key`, `event_category`, and minimal normalized content fields\n  - repeat capture remains idempotent\n  - growing transcript appends only new envelopes\n  - missing transcript list still backfills from stored records\n  - redaction still applies to normalized fields and `source_record`\n- `cargo check -p but --features agentlog`\n- `cargo fmt --check`\n- `cargo clippy -p but-agentlog --all-targets --no-deps`\n\n## Assumptions\n- The POC remains local-only and hidden behind the `agentlog` feature